We can execute commands and shell scripts on Visual Studio code in Windows if we deployed Linux using WSL

Steps:
  1.Open PowerShell in Admin Mode
  2.Open CentOS Terminal
  3.Run:  wsl -l -v
  4.Set Default Distro using : wsl -s distro_name
  5.Open Visual Studio Code
  6.Open Required folder
  7.Open terminal and then type bash and hit enter   
